@startuml figure-3-4-sequence-book-appointment
title Figure 3.4 — Sequence: Patient requests an appointment\n(happy path + 409 Conflict on slot collision)

skinparam dpi 150
skinparam defaultFontName Cambria
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #E7EEF2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #1F2937
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #94A3B8
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #FEF3C7
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #92400E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
skinparam noteBorderColor #A16207
skinparam ArrowColor #334155
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12

actor       "Patient"                        as Patient
participant "Browser\n(Next.js 16)"          as Browser
participant "AppointmentsController\n(NestJS)" as Ctrl
participant "AppointmentsBookings\nService"   as Svc
participant "PrismaService\n(5.22)"          as Prisma
database    "PostgreSQL 16"                  as DB
participant "Notifications\nService"          as Notif
actor       "Doctor\n(student)"               as Doctor

== 1. Patient initiates booking ==

Patient  -> Browser : Click "Book this slot"\non slot browser
activate Browser

Browser  -> Ctrl    : POST /appointments/book\nbody: { slotId, doctorId, clinicCaseId }\nheader: Authorization: Bearer <JWT>
activate Ctrl

note right of Ctrl
  @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)
  ValidationPipe runs class-validator on the DTO
  before the controller body executes.
end note

== 2. Service opens a Prisma $transaction ==

Ctrl -> Svc : bookAppointment(userId, dto)
activate Svc

Svc  -> Prisma : $transaction(async (tx) => ... )
activate Prisma

Prisma -> DB : SELECT slot\nWHERE id = $1\nFOR UPDATE  (row lock)
activate DB
DB --> Prisma : slot row
deactivate DB

== 3. Decide based on slot status ==

alt slot.status = OPEN (happy path)

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE AvailabilitySlot\nSET status = 'BOOKED'\nWHERE id = $1
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  Prisma -> DB : INSERT INTO Appointment\n(slotId, doctorId, patientId, clinicCaseId,\n status='PENDING')
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : appointment row
  deactivate DB

  Prisma -> DB : INSERT INTO AppointmentEvent\n(type='REQUESTED', ...)
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  Svc -> Notif : create(doctorId,\n  "New appointment request")
  activate Notif
  Notif -> Prisma : insert Notification row\n(inside the same tx)
  Prisma -> DB : INSERT INTO Notification ...
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB
  Notif --> Svc : ok
  deactivate Notif

  Prisma --> Svc  : tx commit
  deactivate Prisma

  Svc  --> Ctrl   : appointment DTO
  deactivate Svc
  Ctrl --> Browser : 201 Created\n{ appointment, statusPill: 'PENDING' }
  deactivate Ctrl
  Browser --> Patient : success toast + status pill
  deactivate Browser

  Notif -->> Doctor : in-app + email\n"New appointment request"

else slot.status = BOOKED (collision — concurrent booking)

  Prisma --> Svc : abort
  deactivate Prisma
  Svc  --> Ctrl  : throw ConflictException
  deactivate Svc
  Ctrl --> Browser : 409 Conflict\n{ message: 'Slot already booked' }
  deactivate Ctrl
  Browser --> Patient : "This slot was just\ntaken — pick another"
  deactivate Browser

end

note over Prisma, DB
  The entire branch above runs inside ONE Prisma $transaction.
  Either the slot update + appointment insert + AppointmentEvent + Notification all
  commit, or none do. This guarantees no double-booking under load (NFR-10).
end note

@enduml
